so Dad can’t poke any holes in it.

244
00:11:58,824 --> 00:12:00,510
Unless it’s a donut.

245
00:12:00,534 --> 00:12:02,510
- What?
- What? Donut?

246
00:12:02,534 --> 00:12:04,824
You know, if it’s a donut,
it needs to have a hole in the middle!

247
00:12:05,701 --> 00:12:07,051
You’re so silly, Andres!

248
00:12:07,075 --> 00:12:09,926
- Hey!
- Oh, my loves! Hi!

249
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:12,265
What is this donut
talk I hear about?

250
00:12:13,617 --> 00:12:15,800
I just saw the donuts at work!

251
00:12:15,824 --> 00:12:17,992
Hungry!
Atasha just got hungry for donuts.

252
00:12:20,871 --> 00:12:21,871
Hey!

253
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:24,451
Can’t you see the sign,
do not block the driveway!

254
00:12:24,576 --> 00:12:26,367
- Oh
- Look at these people.

255
00:12:26,534 --> 00:12:29,115
Hold up, we don’t have a car!

256
00:12:31,824 --> 00:12:33,824
Kuya, should I place it here?

257
00:12:35,175 --> 00:12:37,134
You’re all jokes, Iskineport!

258
00:12:37,159 --> 00:12:39,409
But we do need
some living things!

259
00:12:39,824 --> 00:12:41,534
Can’t you see I’m working here?

260
00:12:43,659 --> 00:12:44,824
- Kuya.
- Mmm?

261
00:12:45,451 --> 00:12:48,492
I wanted to ask something.

262
00:12:52,049 --> 00:12:54,925
If this is about money,
don’t talk to me.

263
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:55,950
Hmm?

264
00:12:56,437 --> 00:12:57,729
We’re struggling right now,
struggling.

265
00:12:58,011 --> 00:12:59,011
No money talk.

266
00:12:59,824 --> 00:13:01,824
It’s not about money, Kuya.

267
00:13:02,193 --> 00:13:03,193
What is it, then?

268
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:05,910
It’s about moolah.

269
00:13:06,984 --> 00:13:09,984
Money, moolah,
whatever that is, don’t.

270
00:13:10,451 --> 00:13:11,492
I said we’re struggling.

271
00:13:12,214 --> 00:13:13,907
Struggling.
If you wanna talk about money,

272
00:13:13,932 --> 00:13:15,652
we have nothing to talk about,
because we don’t have money.

273
00:13:15,992 --> 00:13:18,176
I just wanted to
ask for an increase-

274
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,492
See! I just said no money!

275
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:20,993
It’s just five k!

276
00:13:21,992 --> 00:13:23,552
We can’t!
We really can not.

277
00:13:23,576 --> 00:13:24,576
Four k?

278
00:13:24,659 --> 00:13:25,800
- No.
- Three k?

279
00:13:25,824 --> 00:13:27,242
- Nope.
- One k?

280
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,200
One k?

281
00:13:30,534 --> 00:13:32,367
You know what, I really can’t.

282
00:13:32,609 --> 00:13:35,361
I’m thinking about it,
but if I do give you an increase,

283
00:13:35,394 --> 00:13:36,799
even if it’s just a tiny amount,

284
00:13:36,824 --> 00:13:39,118
we’re gonna have to
close down our little bakery.

285
00:13:39,492 --> 00:13:40,824
We really can’t.

286
00:13:41,784 --> 00:13:43,343
- Is that so?
- It’s really hard now.

287
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:47,360
If you give me even just one k,
we could lose the bakery?

288
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:48,743
We’re gonna be all out?

289
00:13:48,784 --> 00:13:50,242
It’s really,
really hard right now.

290
00:13:51,159 --> 00:13:53,608
Okay, how about,

291
00:13:55,902 --> 00:13:57,409
you deduct five
k from my salary?

292
00:13:57,743 --> 00:13:58,760
I’m fine with it!

293
00:13:58,784 --> 00:13:59,800
- Five k?
- Yeah!

294
00:13:59,824 --> 00:14:02,875
I can’t do that, no. I’m embarrassed,
but it would be a big help!

295
00:14:04,824 --> 00:14:06,635
Anything to help us!

296
00:14:06,659 --> 00:14:07,677
Well, thank you!

297
00:14:07,701 --> 00:14:08,824
How much is my salary again?

298
00:14:09,078 --> 00:14:10,495
- Five.
- Five k?

299
00:14:11,325 --> 00:14:12,325
Thank you!

300
00:14:12,534 --> 00:14:14,554
Thank you, thank you! Wait here,
I need to let them know about this!

301
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,542
So I’m gonna be
working for free?

302
00:14:21,451 --> 00:14:22,451
Iskineport!

303
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:25,322
Where are you?

304
00:14:25,824 --> 00:14:27,093
I’m right here.

305
00:14:27,117 --> 00:14:29,800
Don’t pretend like you don’t see me,
you heard me the first time!

306
00:14:29,824 --> 00:14:31,010
I’ve just got so many issues.

307
00:14:31,034 --> 00:14:33,159
Why? What’s up?
Did you ask for a salary increase?

308
00:14:33,659 --> 00:14:34,743
Has Aga responded already?

309
00:14:34,824 --> 00:14:35,843
- Yes.
- Really?

310
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:37,176
- Yes.
- He’s giving you an increase?

311
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,492
He agreed

312
00:14:38,743 --> 00:14:41,409
to take off five k
from my salary.

313
00:14:41,617 --> 00:14:42,617
Bingo!

314
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:43,916
Idiot!

315
00:14:46,923 --> 00:14:48,091
That’s a great idea, Orb!

316
00:14:48,824 --> 00:14:51,324
Put a spin on your best seller!

317
00:14:51,923 --> 00:14:54,216
Actually that’s a common
practice in the food industry.

318
00:14:54,677 --> 00:14:57,052
But it’s risky!

319
00:14:59,051 --> 00:15:01,551
Your best seller
might be ruined.

320
00:15:02,266 --> 00:15:04,890
But people might get fed
up if there’s nothing new.

321
00:15:06,554 --> 00:15:09,395
So, what do we want?

322
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:12,284
I don’t know, too.
What do you think, Orb?

323
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:17,633
Two words: Fruity ensaymada!

324
00:15:18,159 --> 00:15:20,800
- I like that!
- Right? Right?

325
00:15:20,824 --> 00:15:24,824
Just from the name, you’ll know
what’s new, it’s easy to understand,

326
00:15:25,221 --> 00:15:26,430
and it will be easy to market!

327
00:15:26,784 --> 00:15:27,824
That’s wonderful!

328
00:15:28,451 --> 00:15:30,677
It will be more wonderful
if you have free samples!

329
00:15:30,701 --> 00:15:33,701
No, no, no. It doesn’t
have to be free.

330
00:15:33,883 --> 00:15:34,883
We’ll do it like this

331
00:15:35,194 --> 00:15:38,403
for every one hundred
peso-worth of purchase,

332
00:15:38,743 --> 00:15:42,135
they get one piece
of fruity ensaymada.

333
00:15:42,159 --> 00:15:44,010
- Oh, nice!
- How’s that?

334
00:15:44,034 --> 00:15:45,824
- Wow!
- That’s a good idea!

335
00:15:46,117 --> 00:15:49,701
But we have one problem.

336
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:51,977
How do we convince Dad?

337
00:16:05,117 --> 00:16:06,743
- What’s that?
- Kuya, you’re here!

338
00:16:06,977 --> 00:16:09,395
- What
- Tada!

339
00:16:09,824 --> 00:16:14,034
This is our new large pandesal!

340
00:16:14,325 --> 00:16:15,824
- Large?
- Yes!

341
00:16:16,824 --> 00:16:17,959
This is large?

342
00:16:17,984 --> 00:16:19,194
How is this large?

343
00:16:19,824 --> 00:16:22,159
Well, I heard we’re
losing profit,

344
00:16:22,743 --> 00:16:26,659
so I reduced a bit on
our large pandesal.

345
00:16:27,075 --> 00:16:30,325
Our smallest one looks
like a tiny molecule,

346
00:16:30,701 --> 00:16:32,427
it’s like you can mix it in
sugar and it’s unnoticeable.

347
00:16:32,451 --> 00:16:34,884
Well at least, your bread
is in the coffee already.

348
00:16:34,908 --> 00:16:36,409
Iskineport, you have
nothing good to say.

349
00:16:36,854 --> 00:16:38,911
It’s not right to skimp on
the ingredients, and then the

350
00:16:38,936 --> 00:16:40,912
clients will end up with
less than what they paid for.

351
00:16:40,937 --> 00:16:43,230
Can’t you see that’s
too small for a large size?

352
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:45,135
You want it to be larger?

353
00:16:45,159 --> 00:16:47,719
How’s that supposed to be considered large,
are we looking at the same thing?

354
00:16:47,743 --> 00:16:49,824
Ssshhh, sssh! Look!

355
00:17:02,409 --> 00:17:03,409
See!

356
00:17:03,592 --> 00:17:04,967
Large pandesal!

357
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:07,130
See?

358
00:17:07,617 --> 00:17:09,824
This is what it looks like before,
and after blowing into it.

359
00:17:10,159 --> 00:17:11,843
- Taste it!
- How did that happen?

360
00:17:11,867 --> 00:17:13,051
I said taste it!

361
00:17:13,075 --> 00:17:15,824
Aside from its bigger size,
taste it and see!

362
00:17:15,908 --> 00:17:16,908
What?

363
00:17:19,824 --> 00:17:20,824
Why does it taste like laing?

364
00:17:21,492 --> 00:17:24,867
Well, of course, I blew into it,
and I had laing for lunch!

365
00:17:25,228 --> 00:17:27,050
Now, whatever my
previous meal would be,

366
00:17:27,075 --> 00:17:29,135
that would be the pandesal
flavor of the day!

367
00:17:29,159 --> 00:17:30,824
You’re full of crap, you know?

368
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:32,908
- Why?!
- You can’t do that!

369
00:17:33,284 --> 00:17:34,908
What are you going
to call that, then?

370
00:17:35,576 --> 00:17:37,343
Well, a blown-up large pandesal!

371
00:17:37,367 --> 00:17:39,284
This is our pandesal de balloon!

372
00:17:39,743 --> 00:17:40,824
- Pandesal de balloon!
- Dad!

373
00:17:41,824 --> 00:17:42,824
What?!

374
00:17:43,451 --> 00:17:45,464
Ah... Andres has something to say.

375
00:17:46,014 --> 00:17:47,682
- What now?!
- Keep up the good work!

376
00:17:49,534 --> 00:17:52,367
Why are you raising your voice at the kids,
they’re your kids for crying out loud!

377
00:17:52,824 --> 00:17:54,824
What do you mean raising my voice,
I just asked what they wanted!

378
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:56,824
- And you didn’t raise your voice?
- I wasn’t shouting!

379
00:17:57,977 --> 00:17:59,520
Hey! Leave now!

380
00:17:59,891 --> 00:18:01,890
Sssht! Why are you raising
your voice at my kids?

381
00:18:02,576 --> 00:18:05,217
You just said you weren’t screaming,
but that was how you sounded!

382
00:18:06,117 --> 00:18:07,743
Chef K, one of that please.

383
00:18:09,992 --> 00:18:10,992
This?

384
00:18:11,784 --> 00:18:13,159
No, not that one. Not that.

385
00:18:13,824 --> 00:18:14,824
- Which one?
- This one, this, this.

386
00:18:16,824 --> 00:18:17,824
This one?

387
00:18:18,325 --> 00:18:19,325
This?

388
00:18:19,534 --> 00:18:20,534
Not that.

389
00:18:20,534 --> 00:18:21,659
This, this, this one!

390
00:18:22,824 --> 00:18:23,824
Not that one!

391
00:18:23,824 --> 00:18:24,824
Ah, this one?

392
00:18:25,159 --> 00:18:26,159
This one?

393
00:18:26,284 --> 00:18:27,284
This?

394
00:18:27,659 --> 00:18:28,659
No, not that one!

395
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:29,950
- What?
- This one, this one!

396
00:18:30,117 --> 00:18:31,175
- What?
- This!

397
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,200
What do you want?

398
00:18:32,824 --> 00:18:34,050
Do you have a death
wish or something?

399
00:18:34,075 --> 00:18:35,800
You’re getting annoying!

400
00:18:35,824 --> 00:18:37,800
- I don’t!
- You’ve been at this for a while!

401
00:18:37,824 --> 00:18:39,760
- Let me do it, let me.
- Which one? This one!

402
00:18:39,784 --> 00:18:40,784
Let me do it! Let me!

403
00:18:41,284 --> 00:18:43,760
Can’t you see I’m exhausted?
You’re playing with me.

404
00:18:43,784 --> 00:18:44,950
- Which one?
- This one?

405
00:18:45,576 --> 00:18:46,635
Not that one, sir!

406
00:18:46,659 --> 00:18:47,800
- This?
- This, this, this, this?

407
00:18:47,824 --> 00:18:49,593
Not that one, sir! Oh my god!

408
00:18:49,617 --> 00:18:51,284
This one, this, this one?

409
00:18:51,617 --> 00:18:52,719
- Chef K!
- Yeah?

410
00:18:52,743 --> 00:18:54,824
The bread that I like isn’t here.
I’m sorry.

411
00:18:55,992 --> 00:18:58,534
You exhausted me, you pointed to
a lot of bread and you bought nothing!

412
00:19:01,159 --> 00:19:05,926
This day is getting frustrating!
I haven’t sold anything.

413
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:08,200
- Hi, Chef K!
- Stop annoying me, please!

414
00:19:08,824 --> 00:19:11,534
Can’t you see I’m busy? Annoying customers
have been coming around left and right!

415
00:19:11,824 --> 00:19:13,415
- Stop it right now!
- Oh okay,

416
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,800
- I’ll just come back Chef K.
- Hey!

417
00:19:14,824 --> 00:19:16,354
Cha. Cha-cha. Cha-cha!

418
00:19:16,379 --> 00:19:17,552
It’s okay! If you’re busy,
I’ll just come.

419
00:19:17,577 --> 00:19:19,427
No, no, no! I’m not busy!

420
00:19:19,451 --> 00:19:20,510
Look I’ve got no sales,
look no one’s even looking.

421
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:21,824
- I see.
- No one.

422
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,200
If it’s you, it’s fine!

423
00:19:23,824 --> 00:19:24,824
No one’s here. No one.

424
00:19:24,849 --> 00:19:27,760
Okay then. Let me ask you something,
would it be okay with you

425
00:19:27,784 --> 00:19:30,800
if I ask who your
ingredient supplier is?

426
00:19:30,824 --> 00:19:33,983
Our supplier has become
so costly for us,

427
00:19:34,008 --> 00:19:36,242
so our overhead has been
shooting up as well.

428
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:38,824
Maybe we can get from your supplier too?
Maybe they’re cheaper?

429
00:19:43,451 --> 00:19:44,451
Should I help her?

430
00:19:45,997 --> 00:19:49,332
If I help her,
Aga’s bakery will profit.

431
00:19:50,199 --> 00:19:51,718
If that bakery profits,
he’ll be able to pay me,

432
00:19:51,743 --> 00:19:53,010
and he won’t be indebted
to me anymore.

433
00:19:53,034 --> 00:19:54,950
No, I don’t want that to happen.

434
00:19:55,284 --> 00:19:56,284
I can’t let it.

435
00:19:57,284 --> 00:19:58,492
But on the other hand,
it’s Cha-cha asking.

436
00:19:59,534 --> 00:20:00,534
Cha-cha!

437
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:01,824
Cha-cha of my life!

438
00:20:02,992 --> 00:20:03,992
It can't be!

439
00:20:04,534 --> 00:20:05,701
What am I going to do?

440
00:20:05,966 --> 00:20:06,966
What?

441
00:20:06,991 --> 00:20:10,075
Chef K, are you okay?

442
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:13,093
- Yes, I’m fine!
- Are you?

443
00:20:13,117 --> 00:20:14,867
Yes I am, don’t worry.
I was just thinking about your question.

444
00:20:15,492 --> 00:20:19,351
I was thinking, yes it is much
cheaper from my supplier.

445
00:20:19,617 --> 00:20:20,617
It is?

446
00:20:21,175 --> 00:20:22,175
Do you want me
to come with you?

447
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,218
Oh, no need,
that’s totally fine.

448
00:20:24,242 --> 00:20:27,492
Just send me the address,
and I’ll go alone.

449
00:20:28,346 --> 00:20:29,346
Address?

450
00:20:30,004 --> 00:20:31,254
I forgot the address.

451
00:20:32,224 --> 00:20:33,683
So how do you go there?

452
00:20:33,930 --> 00:20:36,014
I just follow my heart.

453
00:20:37,284 --> 00:20:38,325
You know what, Cha-cha,

454
00:20:38,908 --> 00:20:40,824
when you follow your heart,

455
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:42,409
you won’t get lost.

456
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:45,593
What the heck am I saying!

457
00:20:45,617 --> 00:20:47,135
I’m so sorry! I’m sorry!

458
00:20:47,159 --> 00:20:48,784
I was thinking about
the ingredients.

459
00:20:49,117 --> 00:20:52,534
There’s a church nearby and then
you’ll see a wet market, a bit crowded.

460
00:20:52,824 --> 00:20:54,701
- Really?
- No, I really should come with you.

461
00:20:54,824 --> 00:20:56,510
- I don’t want you to get lost.
- I’ll come with you.

462
00:20:56,534 --> 00:20:58,117
- Are you sure?
- Absolutely!

463
00:20:58,824 --> 00:21:01,800
Okay, I’ll just get my things,
if that’s okay with you?

464
00:21:01,824 --> 00:21:04,593
Super okay! Anything for you!

465
00:21:04,617 --> 00:21:06,824
Alright! Thank you Chef K,
see you later!

466
00:21:10,917 --> 00:21:12,293
She’s so beautiful!

467
00:21:15,122 --> 00:21:16,996
Why isn’t she mine?

468
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:21,051
What does Aga have
that I don’t?

469
00:21:21,075 --> 00:21:23,824
Do I not possess
the charm he does?

470
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,576
No, no, no, no you don’t!

471
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:30,075
You said that in unison and
didn’t miss a beat! You’re all rude!

472
00:21:30,284 --> 00:21:32,024
Stop eavesdropping,
you nosy people!

473
00:21:41,034 --> 00:21:44,242
Is that your scent trailing, Chef K?

474
00:21:44,743 --> 00:21:45,800
- You smell so good!
- What the?

475
00:21:45,824 --> 00:21:48,442
I thought there was a
patron saint being paraded,

476
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:49,467
turns out it was just you!

477
00:21:49,492 --> 00:21:51,427
- Look at you all so handsome!
- Will you please stop?

478
00:21:51,451 --> 00:21:54,824
Don’t get too excited!
It’s just me!

479
00:21:55,276 --> 00:21:56,460
Also, can you stay a bit far back,

480
00:21:56,492 --> 00:22:00,576
I don’t want people thinking
we’re exclusively dating.

481
00:22:00,824 --> 00:22:02,719
Stay there!

482
00:22:02,744 --> 00:22:07,785
I’m so sorry. Chef K,
you get cuter when you’re irate.

483
00:22:08,824 --> 00:22:12,593
You look very dashing today!
All dressed up!

484
00:22:12,617 --> 00:22:13,743
Oh, stop it!

485
00:22:14,492 --> 00:22:17,260
Who are you dressed up for, Chef K?

486
00:22:17,284 --> 00:22:18,284
It’s none of your business!

487
00:22:19,059 --> 00:22:20,059
Is it for me?

488
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:21,943
Hi, Chef K!

489
00:23:17,617 --> 00:23:20,824
This thug! How about
I square this guy up?!

490
00:23:21,367 --> 00:23:22,825
That hotel waiter!

491
00:23:23,659 --> 00:23:26,409
That was my moment
and he ruined it!

492
00:23:28,325 --> 00:23:29,325
Chef K!

493
00:23:30,284 --> 00:23:31,284
Chef K!

494
00:23:33,701 --> 00:23:34,950
- Wow!
- You’re coming?

495
00:23:35,230 --> 00:23:36,561
- What?
- You’re coming? With us?

496
00:23:37,617 --> 00:23:38,800
Yeah, I just got surprised
with your outfit!

497
00:23:38,824 --> 00:23:40,200
Looks like all you need
is a riding horse!

498
00:23:41,325 --> 00:23:42,325
You look great!

499
00:23:42,534 --> 00:23:43,635
Go on, say things.

500
00:23:43,659 --> 00:23:45,719
No! I mean it! Handsome!

501
00:23:45,743 --> 00:23:50,135
No, but really, I just want
to thank you, because

502
00:23:50,159 --> 00:23:54,784
I know that although our
bake houses are competitors,

503
00:23:55,367 --> 00:24:00,743
you still value our friendship over it
and are helping us through our struggle.

504
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,200
Thank you.

505
00:24:03,824 --> 00:24:05,093
- What are you doing? Hey!
- I want to thank you!

506
00:24:05,118 --> 00:24:06,370
- It’s fine, it’s fine!
- Thank you!

507
00:24:06,395 --> 00:24:08,701
I said it’s fine!
I said it’s fine!

508
00:24:08,824 --> 00:24:10,325
But how about her?

509
00:24:10,824 --> 00:24:12,800
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

510
00:24:12,824 --> 00:24:14,825
Let me go, it’s Cha-cha’s turn!

511
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:18,074
First, you will see the fruits.

512
00:24:18,453 --> 00:24:19,994
Count on every fruit.

513
00:24:20,286 --> 00:24:23,077
Apple, Kiwi, and Mango.

514
00:24:23,357 --> 00:24:25,565
This fruity ensaymada
tastes so good!

515
00:24:29,824 --> 00:24:30,824
High five!

516
00:24:33,534 --> 00:24:34,801
Kidding!

517
00:24:34,825 --> 00:24:37,492
Oh, it’s like that?
We’re gonna be like that?

518
00:24:38,034 --> 00:24:39,284
He said he was kidding!

519
00:24:40,076 --> 00:24:44,243
But wait a minute, do you really
think our customers will like this?

520
00:24:44,743 --> 00:24:46,843
Yup, but there’s only
one way to find out for real!

521
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:48,719
You’re absolutely right!

522
00:24:48,743 --> 00:24:50,159
Nobody’s perfect!

523
00:24:50,492 --> 00:24:52,800
During your times of suffering,
when you see one

524
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:55,824
set of footprints, it was
then that I carried you

525
00:24:58,367 --> 00:24:59,800
Here you go, thank you!

526
00:24:59,824 --> 00:25:00,825
Thank you!

527
00:25:01,034 --> 00:25:02,617
Andres, Andres, look
here, look, look!

528
00:25:03,659 --> 00:25:04,659
Yes!

529
00:25:04,824 --> 00:25:06,468
Kuya, kuya, kuya,
smile for the camera!

530
00:25:06,492 --> 00:25:07,492
Thank you!

531
00:25:07,701 --> 00:25:08,701
Thank you!

532
00:25:08,726 --> 00:25:09,800
You’re so good at this, Tash!

533
00:25:09,824 --> 00:25:11,510
Why, thank you!

534
00:25:11,534 --> 00:25:12,617
- Thank you!
- Thank you, keep safe!

535
00:25:12,867 --> 00:25:15,381
Thank you, see us again!

536
00:25:21,117 --> 00:25:23,824
What’s the update,
are we gonna be switching suppliers?

537
00:25:25,010 --> 00:25:26,511
The new suppliers
should be okay.

538
00:25:26,824 --> 00:25:30,492
They’re relatively cheaper,
but if you count shipping,

539
00:25:31,391 --> 00:25:33,433
it’s all the same,
the fees get higher.

540
00:25:33,617 --> 00:25:34,617
Goodness!

541
00:25:35,214 --> 00:25:36,673
That’s what I really don’t like!

542
00:25:37,159 --> 00:25:39,075
I’m helping, but it looks like
I’m coming out as the bad one.

543
00:25:39,784 --> 00:25:40,867
Do you just wanna square up?

544
00:25:41,159 --> 00:25:43,635
- Wait, wait! Chef, chef!
- Whoever wins gets Charlene!

545
00:25:43,659 --> 00:25:44,659
Okay?!

546
00:25:44,824 --> 00:25:46,510
Why are you getting so upset?

547
00:25:46,534 --> 00:25:48,427
- Who are you upset at?
- I am upset!

548
00:25:48,451 --> 00:25:49,576
Towards whom?!

549
00:25:49,824 --> 00:25:51,800
- The supplier!
- Oh okay.

550
00:25:51,824 --> 00:25:52,824
I’m upset at him!

551
00:25:53,492 --> 00:25:56,908
I am giving them business,
giving them additional income,

552
00:25:57,617 --> 00:25:59,950
and they barely want to adjust!

553
00:26:00,242 --> 00:26:01,242
Who does he think he is?!

554
00:26:01,824 --> 00:26:04,800
I’m getting so frustrated
I wanna punch them in the face!

555
00:26:04,824 --> 00:26:06,576
- Who?!
- The supplier!

556
00:26:07,325 --> 00:26:08,492
I wanna punch him in the face.

557
00:26:08,617 --> 00:26:09,824
I’m so mad!

558
00:26:09,825 --> 00:26:10,992
So, so upset!

559
00:26:16,908 --> 00:26:22,801
For every P100 purchase,
you get a fruity ensaymada.

560
00:26:22,825 --> 00:26:25,800
Don’t crowd us, don’t crowd!

561
00:26:25,824 --> 00:26:26,824
What is this?

562
00:26:27,034 --> 00:26:28,034
Iskineport!

563
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,200
Can’t you see I’m busy?

564
00:26:31,225 --> 00:26:32,600
What’s happening here?

565
00:26:32,625 --> 00:26:35,301
In every one hundred thousand
peso purchase, they

566
00:26:35,325 --> 00:26:37,926
get one fruity ensaymada,
the customers love it!

567
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:38,950
One hundred thousand?!

568
00:26:39,117 --> 00:26:40,800
- I mean one hundred pesos!
- Oh!

569
00:26:40,824 --> 00:26:43,176
The customers love it so much,
this is our third batch!

570
00:26:43,342 --> 00:26:44,467
Fruity ensaymada?

571
00:26:44,492 --> 00:26:45,492
Yeah!

572
00:26:45,824 --> 00:26:47,534
Stop trying to be so humble,
you can gloat!

573
00:26:47,784 --> 00:26:51,218
This is the ensaymada
that has fruit toppings!

574
00:26:51,242 --> 00:26:54,179
Strawberry, kiwi, this one!

575
00:26:54,242 --> 00:26:56,284
In every one hundred peso purchase,
you get a free one!

576
00:26:56,784 --> 00:26:59,451
Didn’t your kids tell you?

577
00:27:00,325 --> 00:27:01,992
My love, what’s he saying?

578
00:27:02,242 --> 00:27:08,075
Hang on a second, didn’t Atasha
and Andres tell you about this?

579
00:27:21,278 --> 00:27:25,611
Why didn’t you tell me that’s
what you were planning to do?

580
00:27:25,784 --> 00:27:26,784
We tried, Dad.

581
00:27:26,992 --> 00:27:30,242
But you were so hot-headed.

582
00:27:30,922 --> 00:27:34,799
When we approached you,
you already sounded so heated!

583
00:27:34,824 --> 00:27:36,908
I sound heated?!

584
00:27:37,824 --> 00:27:38,824
Heated?

585
00:27:39,293 --> 00:27:40,917
My voice does not sound heated.

586
00:27:41,617 --> 00:27:44,635
That’s what I’m trying to say.
I mean to say, that’s my modulated voice.

587
00:27:44,666 --> 00:27:46,986
What I’m trying to say, kids,

588
00:27:47,284 --> 00:27:50,576
is that ensaymada
is our best-seller,

589
00:27:50,824 --> 00:27:52,760
why would you put
a spin on that?

590
00:27:52,908 --> 00:27:56,343
Dad, what we need is
innovation in our products.

591
00:27:56,367 --> 00:27:58,135
Before the people even
have a chance to grow tired

592
00:27:58,159 --> 00:28:00,123
of our existing offer,
let’s put a twist on it!

593
00:28:00,659 --> 00:28:01,659
- Right
- Yeah!

594
00:28:02,063 --> 00:28:03,800
- Our sales shook up today!
- Yeah!

595
00:28:03,824 --> 00:28:06,811
So you mean are you..

596
00:28:07,281 --> 00:28:09,396
do you mean to say you’ve
been having promos every day?

597
00:28:09,824 --> 00:28:12,124
That’s not right,
you can’t have promos everyday.

598
00:28:12,701 --> 00:28:14,367
It’s not sustainable.

599
00:28:14,824 --> 00:28:16,605
Tash, Andres,
can’t you see that?

600
00:28:16,630 --> 00:28:19,231
Don’t you see that there are
costs behind all of this.

601
00:28:19,367 --> 00:28:21,824
Have you even thought about the
ingredients that you’re going to use?

602
00:28:22,180 --> 00:28:23,889
Those are so expensive!

603
00:28:26,824 --> 00:28:28,784
- Hey, speak up!
- I’m trying!

604
00:28:29,242 --> 00:28:30,242
- Dad
- Sssht!

605
00:28:30,824 --> 00:28:32,093
Leave me alone, please.

606
00:28:32,117 --> 00:28:34,824
Please. I want to be alone
with my thoughts Please.

607
00:28:36,701 --> 00:28:37,743
Okay, Tash, Dres?

608
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,874
Thank you very much, thank you.

609
00:29:02,964 --> 00:29:04,340
Oh, Atasha!

610
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:06,910
Andres!

611
00:29:19,236 --> 00:29:20,903
I’ll take a video of this.

612
00:29:21,451 --> 00:29:22,451
Mmm!

613
00:29:24,451 --> 00:29:25,784
Mmm!

614
00:29:27,159 --> 00:29:29,800
It’s good, isn’t it?

615
00:29:29,824 --> 00:29:30,824
Lola Maxi!

616
00:29:31,824 --> 00:29:33,284
There you go, that’s it!
Swallow it fully!

617
00:29:35,992 --> 00:29:37,409
Beautiful!

618
00:29:38,743 --> 00:29:43,534
The kids are just doing
their best to help us.

619
00:29:44,117 --> 00:29:45,824
I get that.

620
00:29:46,580 --> 00:29:48,131
I understand that
they want to help,

621
00:29:48,284 --> 00:29:49,800
they’re doing what they can.

622
00:29:49,824 --> 00:29:51,123
There’s nothing bad about that,

623
00:29:51,824 --> 00:29:56,325
but I just feel like there should
be someone making the decisions.

624
00:29:56,817 --> 00:29:59,124
So, I’m okay with them
trying to help,

625
00:29:59,156 --> 00:30:03,492
there’s nothing wrong with that,
but who makes the decisions?

626
00:30:03,824 --> 00:30:06,824
That’s what they’re saying,
they’re scared of you.

627
00:30:07,617 --> 00:30:08,824
Whose side are you on?

628
00:30:08,867 --> 00:30:10,824
There shouldn’t be
any sides to this.

629
00:30:11,743 --> 00:30:13,075
We’re supposed to be one team.

630
00:30:16,492 --> 00:30:22,492
You know how in every
dish or recipe that we cook,

631
00:30:22,825 --> 00:30:26,284
there are many ingredients
that go into it no matter how little,

632
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:29,159
there is a contribution for each
ingredient which make the whole dish!

633
00:30:29,824 --> 00:30:33,014
Take away one ingredient

634
00:30:33,039 --> 00:30:36,617
and it’s not the same food,
it’s not even going to look the same.

635
00:30:38,701 --> 00:30:42,800
But they put fruits
on the ensaymada.

636
00:30:42,824 --> 00:30:45,043
Yes, and?

637
00:30:45,492 --> 00:30:49,284
Was the fundamental taste ruined,
or did the fruits compliment it?

638
00:30:56,617 --> 00:30:57,617
Why the face?

639
00:30:58,367 --> 00:31:00,593
Hug me again,
why did you take off your arms?

640
00:31:00,617 --> 00:31:02,051
- Oh, you like it?
- Of course, I do!

641
00:31:02,075 --> 00:31:03,367
- Okay, then!
- Put it there!

642
00:31:04,117 --> 00:31:05,117
Are you feeling better?

643
00:31:05,117 --> 00:31:06,908
Yeah, yeah.

644
00:31:11,824 --> 00:31:15,200
Dad, we’re really really sorry
that we skipped letting you know.

645
00:31:15,824 --> 00:31:16,824
We had two reasons

646
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:18,200
first off,

647
00:31:18,325 --> 00:31:20,593
we wanted to do a
feasibility study of the

648
00:31:20,617 --> 00:31:22,824
product first before
we presented it to you,

649
00:31:22,825 --> 00:31:24,385
so we did a test drive first.

650
00:31:24,409 --> 00:31:25,409
Yeah.

651
00:31:25,434 --> 00:31:28,743
Second reason,
we’re scared to ask permission.

652
00:31:30,409 --> 00:31:31,409
How about you?

653
00:31:32,824 --> 00:31:35,784
Are you just going to let your lawyer
explain everything for you?

654
00:31:35,825 --> 00:31:36,825
Sorry, Dad.

655
00:31:37,138 --> 00:31:38,970
I-it will never happen again.

656
00:31:40,824 --> 00:31:42,409
- Yes.
- You know what, you two,

657
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:45,926
everything you did is
fairly okay with me.

658
00:31:45,950 --> 00:31:50,284
The only thing I would like for you
to do next time is you let me know.

659
00:31:50,917 --> 00:31:53,001
Tell me about your plans.

660
00:31:53,824 --> 00:31:57,824
We’re not saying that we will
always agree with you, okay?

661
00:31:58,495 --> 00:32:01,953
We just want to be
let in on the truth.

662
00:32:02,464 --> 00:32:04,381
No secrets,

663
00:32:10,375 --> 00:32:11,375
Dad

664
00:32:11,701 --> 00:32:12,701
Mom

665
00:32:16,824 --> 00:32:17,824
I have a boyfriend.

666
00:32:19,036 --> 00:32:20,036
You have a what?!

667
00:32:20,617 --> 00:32:21,950
I’m kidding!

668
00:32:22,409 --> 00:32:25,260
- Look at you, you just said no secrets!
- This kid!

669
00:32:25,284 --> 00:32:26,800
Do you want me to have one?

670
00:32:26,824 --> 00:32:28,824
Stop! I get it.

671
00:32:29,534 --> 00:32:31,367
Dad! Have you tried it yet?

672
00:32:31,743 --> 00:32:34,701
Go on, taste it already!

673
00:32:35,108 --> 00:32:36,317
Here we go!

674
00:32:38,242 --> 00:32:39,284
Mmmm.

675
00:32:40,244 --> 00:32:41,494
Tastes different!

676
00:32:42,743 --> 00:32:43,760
Tastes better!

677
00:32:43,784 --> 00:32:44,784
Is it good?

678
00:32:47,973 --> 00:32:48,973
Let me try again!

679
00:33:08,824 --> 00:33:09,992
So, you see!

680
00:33:10,743 --> 00:33:14,010
I can say now that I still
bake better than you do!

681
00:33:14,034 --> 00:33:15,034
Isn’t it true?

682
00:33:16,901 --> 00:33:18,545
Yeah, but this, though!

683
00:33:18,576 --> 00:33:19,576
Who’s the better baker?

684
00:33:19,576 --> 00:33:21,534
- I think it’s I am!
- I know I am!

685
00:33:21,701 --> 00:33:22,701
What

686
00:33:24,034 --> 00:33:27,492
Well just look at my sales, Dad!
High in demand, and in Singapore, too!

687
00:33:29,284 --> 00:33:36,800
Lola Maxi, come here. Stay here with us,
enjoy the moment, don’t just pose and post!

688
00:33:36,824 --> 00:33:40,950
Oh, you kids make me emotional.

689
00:33:41,617 --> 00:33:47,824
I just keep thinking, when the time comes
that I can’t remember anymore,

690
00:33:48,824 --> 00:33:53,010
just show me my posts or
my social media accounts

691
00:33:53,034 --> 00:33:57,510
so I can remember the
good memories like this one!

692
00:33:57,534 --> 00:33:59,534
Awwww, Lola Maxi!

693
00:33:59,824 --> 00:34:01,159
We love you!

694
00:34:01,824 --> 00:34:05,010
That was a great idea,
Lola Maxi is the best!

695
00:34:05,034 --> 00:34:13,325
Your hugs are so warm! Goodness,
I remember your Lolo Roman’s warm hugs!

696
00:34:14,992 --> 00:34:18,385
You know what, his hugs
are the best! But of course,

697
00:34:18,409 --> 00:34:21,701
when he hugs me,
you know what comes right after.

698
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:23,325
Of course!

699
00:34:23,534 --> 00:34:26,824
Gosh, it starts here!

700
00:34:30,992 --> 00:34:34,824
Oh stop, the kids are listening

701
00:34:36,617 --> 00:34:38,824
Look at these people!

702
00:34:40,824 --> 00:34:45,743
That was so good!

703
00:34:45,824 --> 00:34:46,824
- Really?
- Was it really good?

704
00:34:46,824 --> 00:34:49,824
Yes, super! Such a shame
you didn’t get to try it!

705
00:34:50,117 --> 00:34:54,719
But you know what, Dad’s old school ways
are slowly improving.

706
00:34:54,743 --> 00:34:56,824
Could it be because of
my fruity ensaymada idea?

707
00:34:57,034 --> 00:34:58,468
Look at you being
a credit grabber!

708
00:34:58,492 --> 00:34:59,571
What do you mean
a credit grabber?!

709
00:34:59,596 --> 00:35:01,260
Yeah, I was in on that idea!

710
00:35:01,284 --> 00:35:02,284
Remember kuya

711
00:35:02,743 --> 00:35:07,534
In struggles and in happiness,
Pers is the first, Pers is the hero!

712
00:35:12,824 --> 00:35:16,659
When you ruined them,
you owe me nothing.

713
00:35:18,325 --> 00:35:19,884
Um, Mika. What exactly
are you here for?

714
00:35:19,908 --> 00:35:22,093
I’m looking for a job.

715
00:35:22,117 --> 00:35:25,701
Let her stay here
until she can find a job!

716
00:35:25,824 --> 00:35:27,760
Her timing is actually perfect!
Iskineport just got into

717
00:35:27,784 --> 00:35:29,593
an accident, and you have
so many orders to fulfill.

718
00:35:29,617 --> 00:35:31,884
- You’re hired!
- You’re hired!

719
00:35:31,908 --> 00:35:34,093
Why don’t you leave now?
You mean you want to stay here, too?!

720
00:35:34,117 --> 00:35:35,926
Now you want to
replace me for my job?!

721
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:38,677
I have a bad feeling about Mika.

722
00:35:38,701 --> 00:35:39,800
She's a bad person.

723
00:35:39,824 --> 00:35:41,343
Bad people? That beautiful?

724
00:35:41,367 --> 00:35:44,950
I caught them putting a
camera to sneak on me!

725
00:35:45,701 --> 00:35:48,560
It's not because she's good
at the job you're doing,

726
00:35:48,584 --> 00:35:50,051
you're going to discredit him.

727
00:35:50,075 --> 00:35:51,800
Just take a rest
for three months!

728
00:35:51,824 --> 00:35:53,218
It's too long!

729
00:35:53,242 --> 00:35:55,176
You won't be here for
about three months.

730
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:56,534
- I'll leave!
- I'll leave!

731
00:35:56,701 --> 00:35:57,825
- Huh?!
- You'll leave too?!
